text: A warm hello to all you wonderful people, I'm Mira. I ditched my coveted career in dental surgery :toothbrush: to hop on the marketing bandwagon :ferris_wheel: that accommodated for my bizarre 2 am-ideas and allowed me to widen my creative leg space! I am currently working with an agency as a UX-writer :writing_hand: and looking forward to learning from your experiences :sunglasses: and listening to your stories :heart_eyes:. Quite a bit of a generalist professionally, I'd happy to help in any form or function. Cheers! :tada:

We help companies working on autonomous systems (autonomous driving, healthcare, drones…) to better access the data that they need to deliver on the promise of artificial intelligence. #B2B #DeepTech 
I’m glad to be part of this group, I look forward to exchanging on our topics. :v:

Hey everyone — I'm Franklin Morris. I'm a content, comms and brand leader for B2B tech companies. (I just made the move from San Francisco to Texas).

I'm a writer by background with an MFA and BA in creative writing, and I’ve led content teams at high-growth  startups,  agencies and Fortune 50 brands — including IBM, Dell, Oracle, Cisco, 3M, Rackspace, Electronic Arts (EA), Informatica, Argo Group, Sisense and more. I'm excited to be part of this community and connect with you all! :the_horns:

Today I lead content at a startup called *Alloy*. Connect w/ me on LinkedIn here: <http://www.linkedin.com/in/franklinmorris>

Hey everyone! I'm Nahla. Four years ago I was working as a partner account manager at Microsoft MEA. A diagnosis got me thinking about what I was doing and how unhappy I had been so after 14 years if working in sales I decided to stop and start on my way.

I'm now a content writer. I have a BA in English Literature but it's hardly the reason why I'm writing :smiley: I'm a generalist and I kinda like it that way.

I'm happy to be here. I miss having a work community! You can also find me here <http://www.linkedin.com/in/nahlaelkazak|www.linkedin.com/in/nahlaelkazak>
Looking forward to connect with you all!

text:
Hey y'all!
I'm Adam. 10 years ago, I started writing by creating my own affiliate marketing blog and services company. I dropped out of Berkeley after I had huge success but decided I didn't want to continue in that niche and take another path. Today, I'm back to writing my own blog about my life at <http://www.adamsoutside.com|www.adamsoutside.com>. Besides that, I freelance for other websites while I am looking for a more stable career in Content Writing and Copywriting.

Oh yeah, besides Content Writing, I broke into copywriting this year and am quickly building that portfolio. I'd like to say I have a diverse background, from writing top 50 app store descriptions to running a YouTube channel with 60k subscribers. I'm interested in anything marketing and am extremely adaptable. Check out my LinkedIn at <https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamandrewjeski/> and Upwork <https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/~01b8eae8ceb198629c>. I'm looking for work, and if you're not hiring, maybe you'll find my posts useful.

Looking forward to connecting!
Adam
